Detailed Description

Fortran 77 interface definitions for querying the USGS central CA velocity model (USER INTERFACE).

These are the routines that are used to query the USGS central CA velocity model from Fortran 77. See cvmquery.h for the routines to query the velocity model using C. If you are using C++, you should use the VMQuery object directly.

The current defaults for queries are:

  • return all values in a query,
  • query at the maximum resolution of the model
  • 128 MB cache for queries

The default behavior can be modified by calling the appropriate class method, e.g., cencalvm_querytype_f() and cencalvm_cachesize_f().

The general order of use is:

  1. Create query object using cencalvm_createquery_f()
  2. Set filename of database using cencalvm_filename_f()
  3. Optionally, set cache size using cencalvm_cachesize_f()
  4. Open database using cencalvm_open_f()
  5. Query database using cencalvm_query_f()
  6. Close database using cencalvm_close_f()
  7. Destroy query object using cencalvm_destroyquery_f()

The values associated with the error status come from the status of the error handler. See cencalvm::storage::ErrorHandler for what the values mean.

void cencalvm_query_f ( size_t *  handleAddr,
double *  pVals,
const int *  numVals,
const double *  lon,
const double *  lat,
const double *  elev,
int *  err 
)

Query the database.

Warning:
Array for values to be returned must be allocated BEFORE query.
Note:
Longitude and latitude are given in degrees in the WGS84 datum.
Elevation is given in meters with respect to mean sea level.
Values returned include the values in cencalvm::storage::PayloadStruct plus the elevation of topography/bathymetry (ground surface or ocean floor; the query value is 'elevation').
Parameters:
handleAddrAddress of handle to VMQuery object
pValsPointer to computed values (output from query)
numValsNumber of values expected (size of array (preallocated))
lonLongitude of location for query in degrees
latLatitude of location for query in degrees
elevElevation of location wrt MSL in meters
errSet to status of error handler
void cencalvm_queryres_f ( size_t *  handleAddr,
const double *  res,
int *  err 
)

Set query resolution.

Meaning depends on type of query:

  • MAXRES Resolution is not applicable
  • FIXEDRES Query etree at level corresponding to resolution
  • AVGRES Resolution corresponds to minimum period of waves; etree is queried at lavel corresponding to minimum wavelength for shear waves
Parameters:
handleAddrAddress of handle to VMQuery object
resResolution of query.
errSet to status of error handler
void cencalvm_querytype_f ( size_t *  handleAddr,
const int *  queryType,
int *  err 
)

Set query type.

Queries other than maximum resolution require an etree database that has been spatially averaged. This fills in parent octants with the average of its children.

Parameters:
handleAddrAddress of handle to VMQuery object
queryTypeType of query

  • =0 Query at maximum resolution
  • =1 Query at fixed resolution
  • =2 Query at resolution tuned to wavelength of shear waves
errSet to status of error handler
